OL,3,CCoracles in Carmarthen: The 300-year-
OL,4,Cold tradition being kept alive
OL,6,F"Hundreds of years ago Carmarthen was
OL,7,Fthe biggest port in Wales, it would
OL,8,Fimport and export to places all over
OL,9,Fthe world.
OL,11,F"It's estimated about 2,500 people
OL,12,Fgained their earnings from working
OL,13,Falong the River Towy.
OL,15,F"However, when the town welcomed the
OL,16,Frailway that changed it all for the
OL,17,Fport and it closed, but the one thing
OL,18,Fthat remained on the river is the
OL,19,Fcoracle."
