OL,3,CCoracles in Carmarthen: The 300-year-
OL,4,Cold tradition being kept alive
OL,6,FDuring the 18th and 19th centuries,
OL,7,Fcoracle fishing was the main source of
OL,8,Fincome for many families living along
OL,9,Fthe banks of the River Towy. In those
OL,10,Fdays you could expect to see 200 of
OL,11,Fthe small boats on the water but today
OL,12,Fonly eight fishing licenses remain.
OL,14,FDespite the decline in the number of
OL,15,Fcoracles, Malcolm Rees from Carmarthen
OL,16,Fis working hard to keep his family's
OL,17,F300-year-old tradition alive, and that
OL,18,Fis to make the coracles.
