OL,3,CCoracles in Carmarthen: The 300-year-
OL,4,Cold tradition being kept alive
OL,6,FHe said: "My great-grandad was born in
OL,7,F1876, he was the master that taught my
OL,8,Ffather and uncle who have now passed
OL,9,Fit on to me. It was something that I
OL,10,Fgrew up with.
OL,12,F"I was in my late 30s and my father
OL,13,Fwas getting on and I thought it was
OL,14,Ftime I pick up the baton, that's when
OL,15,FI became a coracle maker and it's like
OL,16,Fwith everything, the more you do the
OL,17,Fbetter you get."
