OL,3,CCoracles in Carmarthen: The 300-year-
OL,4,Cold tradition being kept alive
OL,6,FMalcolm added: "The thing about making
OL,7,Fa traditional coracle is they're never
OL,8,Fthe same, they're quite unique so it
OL,9,Fis a craft. There are far better
OL,10,Fcraftsmen than me, but I'm the one
OL,11,Fthat's keeping it burning, really."
OL,13,FWhile most modern coracles in the area
OL,14,Ftoday are made of fibreglass, Malcolm
OL,15,Fcontinues to use the old practice of
OL,16,Finterweaving thin wooden rods to
OL,17,Fcreate the frame of the coracle.
